I'm a low-level systems developer and retro enthusiast. I saw computers from the '70s, '80s and '90s as much simpler, so I spend much of my development time trying to create systems that expose you to the deeper layers of your software stack - early software did this out of necessity, but my programs do it for two very different reasons: education and fun.

I'm not a frontend developer, so this website isn't some flashy design project, but you can reach these pages from 4 different internet protocols, all of which I have implemented from scratch in Nim. See my project 'Quadraserve' if you're curious.

## My projects

