## About me

I am a self-taught software developer, and have been for 6 years. I got started in the space as most do, by learning Python. I still occasionally use Python as it is indeed an excellent language for quick scripting. However, in the time since I began programming, I have become increasingly curious about how exactly my computer executes the code I write.

This has since led me down a rabbit-hole of learning C, and eventually Assembly (albeit for the 6502 and Z80 architectures), which has undoubtedly improved my understanding of the workings of CPUs - but a functioning machine is more than just a CPU. 

So I created the 'Ozpex' family of projects, where I designed and implemented an emulator for an entirely custom computer architecture and have written a BIOS, bootloader, kernel, filesystem and programming language entirely from scratch, all in assembly to run on that system.

